description: An adult and two children have been rescued following a horror crash on one of Sydney's busiest roads, sparking major chaos during the morning peak hour.

title: Britons will save £106K for every Channel migrant deterred from reaching the UK
description: An official analysis of the Government's Illegal Migration Bill said the potential savings could reach £165,000 per person if hotel costs for would-be refugees continue to rise.

title: General blasts Army's outdated vehicles and belief that reservists can replace regulars
description: General Sir Patrick Sanders (pictured) said much of the Army's 'platforms' were 'outdated' and 'not fit for purpose', and derided our reservist force as neither 'capable' nor 'credible'.

title: Labour ditches its £3 billion tech giant tax in  'fifth flip-flop in a month'
description: Labour has quietly ditched a £3billion tax raid on tech giants in what the Tories say is the Opposition's fifth flip-flop in a month. Success of US firms such as Amazon and Facebook have prompted the levy.

title: Nicola Bulley's final hours laid bare
description: In painstaking detail, yesterday's inquest revealed minute-by-minute of Nicola Bulley's final hours - down to the last detail.

title: How Coleen's legal demands could trigger a delicious new chapter in the Wagatha Christie drama
description: Last week, it was announced that Coleen, 37, will be on the cover of Vogue magazine later this year, a pinnacle hitherto unscaled by any mere WAG.

title: Prince William starts UK tour to launch his programme aimed at ending homelessness
description: Prince William started his two-day UK tour today launching his homelessness project Homewards. His first visit was in London, followed by Bournemouth, then Newport.

title: Woman found dead along California freeway 27 years ago is identified as mother-of-four
description: A woman whose body was discovered on a Southern California highway more than 25 years ago has been identified as a 41-year-old mother of four.

title: Ryanair pilot killed in hot air balloon explosion's brother flew beside him
description: Peter Gregory, 25, of the Cotswolds, fell to his death on Sunday when his balloon deflated and crashed into trees, as his brother Dan watched on in horror.

title: New £500-a-pot skin cream from British brand has 30,000 customers on its waiting list
description: A new skin cream from a British brand endorsed by the likes of Victoria Beckham has 30,000 customers on the waiting list - even though it costs nearly £500 for just 100ml.

title: The BBC's portrayal of the working class is 'miserable' claims broadcaster Melvyn Bragg
description: Lord Bragg, 83, the son of a publican who grew up in Carlisle, said: 'I did a book called Back In The Day, which was about my background - white working class.'

title: Elon Musk's mother Maye says fight between billionaire and Mark Zuckerberg 'is canceled'
description: Elon Musk's mother is worried for her son's safety and told people 'don't encourage this match' between him and Mark Zuckerberg before joking that it was canceled.
